\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \i\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Call Lightning
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Evocation [Electricity]
\par Level: Drd 3
\par Components: V, S
\par Casting Time: 10 minutes, plus 1 action per bolt called
\par Range: Long (400 ft. + 40 ft./level)
\par Effect: See text
\par Duration: 10 minutes/level
\par Saving Throw: Reflex half
\par Spell Resistance: Yes
\par To cast call lightning, the character must be in a stormy area (including a whirlwind formed by a djinn or air elemental of 7 HD o
r more). The character is then able to call bolts of lightning as long as the character remains in the stormy area. (The spell ends if the character leaves the stormy area.) The character can call down one bolt every 10 minutes. The character need not cal
l a bolt of lightning immediately\emdash 
other actions, even spellcasting, can be performed. However, the character must use a standard action (concentrating on the spell) to call each bolt. A bolt causes 1d10 points of electrical damage per caster level (maximum 10d10).
\par The bolt of lightning strikes down in a vertical stroke at whatever target point the character chooses, within range (measured from the c
haracter's position at the time). The bolt takes the shortest possible unobstructed path between a nearby cloud and the target. Any creature within a 10-foot radius of the path or the point where the lightning strikes is affected.
\par This spell can be used only outdoors. It does not function indoors, underground, or underwater.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \i\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Calm Animals
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Enchantment (Compulsion) [Mind-Affecting]
\par Level: Animal 1, Drd 1
\par Components: V, S
\par Casting Time: 1 action
\par Range: Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par Targets: Animals, beasts, or magical beasts with Intelligence 1 or 2 within 30 ft. of each other
\par Duration: 1 minute/level
\par Saving Throw: Will negates (see text)
\par Spell Resistance: Yes
\par This spell affects animals, beasts, and magical beasts, rendering them docile and harmless. Only crea
tures with Intelligence scores of 1 or 2 can be affected by this spell. All the subjects must be of the same species and within a 30-foot sphere. Roll 2d4 + caster level to determine the total number of HD affected. Animals trained to attack or guard, dir
e animals, beasts, and magical beasts are allowed saving throws. Animals not trained to attack or guard are not.
\par The affected creatures remain where they are and do not attack or flee. They are not helpless and defend themselves normally if attacked. Any threat breaks the spell on the threatened creatures.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \i\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Calm Emotions
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Enchantment (Compulsion) [Mind-Affecting]
\par Level: Clr 2, Law 2
\par Components: V, S, DF
\par Casting Time: 1 action
\par Range: Medium (100 ft. + 10 ft./level)
\par Targets: 1d6 creatures/level, all of whom must be within 30 ft. of each other
\par Duration: Concentration, up to 1 round/level (D)
\par Saving Throw: Will negates
\par Spell Resistance: Yes
\par This spell calms agitated creatures. The character has no control over the affected creatures, but this spell can stop creatu
res from fighting. Creatures so affected cannot take violent actions (although they can defend themselves) or do anything destructive, except to protect themselves. Any aggressive action or life-threatening damage against calmed creatures immediately brea
ks the spell on the threatened creatures.
\par This spell automatically suppresses (but does not dispel) mind-affecting spells, as well as negating a bard\rquote s ability to inspire courage or a barbarian\rquote s rage. While the calm emotions spell lasts, a suppressed spell
 has no effect. When the calm emotions spell ends, the original spell takes hold of the creature again, provided its duration has not expired in the meantime.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \i\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Cat\rquote s Grace
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Transmutation
\par Level: Brd 2, Sor/Wiz 2
\par Components: V, S, M
\par Casting Time: 1 action
\par Range: Touch
\par Target: Creature touched
\par Duration: 1 hour/level
\par Saving Throw: Will Negates (harmless)
\par Spell Resistance: Yes
\par The spell grants an enhancement bonus to Dexterity of 1d4+1 points.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \i\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Cause Fear
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Necromancy [Fear, Mind-Affecting]
\par Level: Brd 1, Clr 1, Death 1, Sor/Wiz 1
\par Components: V, S
\par Casting Time: 1 action
\par Range: Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par Target: One living creature
\par Duration: 1d4 rounds
\par Saving Throw: Will negates
\par Spell Resistance: Yes
\par The affected creature becomes frightened. It suffers a \endash 2 mo
rale penalty on attack rolls, weapon damage rolls, and saving throws. It flees from the character as well as it can. If unable to flee, the creature may fight. Creatures with 6 or more Hit Dice are immune. Cause fear counters remove fear.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \i\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Chain Lightning
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Evocation [Electricity]
\par Level: Air 6, Sor/Wiz 6
\par Components: V, S, F
\par Casting Time: 1 action
\par Range: Long (400 ft. + 40 ft./level)
\par Targets: One primary target plus one secondary target/level (each must be within 30 ft. of the primary target)
\par Duration: Instantaneous
\par Saving Throw: Reflex half
\par Spell Resistance: Yes
\par This spell creates an electrical discharge from the character's fingertips. Chain lightning strikes one object or creature initially, then arcs to other targets.
\par The bolt deals 1d6 poi
nts of electricity damage per caster level (maximum 20d6) on the primary target. After the bolt strikes, lightning can arc to as many secondary targets as the character has levels. The secondary bolts each strike one target and deal half as many dice of d
a
mage as the primary (rounded down). All subjects can attempt Reflex saving throws for half damage. The character chooses secondary targets as the character likes, but they must all be within 30 feet of the primary target, and no target can be struck more 
than once. The character can choose to affect fewer secondary targets than the maximum.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \i\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Change Self
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Illusion (Glamer)
\par Level: Sor/Wiz 1, Trickery 1
\par Components: V, S
\par Casting Time: 1 action
\par Range: Personal
\par Target: The character
\par Duration: 10 minutes/level (D)
\par The character can make his or herself\emdash including clothing, armor, weapons, and equipment\emdash 
look different. The character can seem 1 foot shorter or taller, thin, fat, or in between. The character cannot change the character's body type.  Otherwise, the extent of the apparent change is up to the character.
\par The spell does not provide the abilities or mannerisms of the chosen form. It does not alter the perceived tactile (touch) or audible (sound) properties of the character or the character's equipment.
\par If the character uses this spell to create a disguise, the character gets a +10 bonus on the Disguise check.
\par Note: Creatures get Will saves to recognize the glamer as an illusion if they interact with it.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \i\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Changestaff
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Transmutation
\par Level: Drd 7, Plant 7
\par Components: V, S, F
\par Casting Time: 1 full round
\par Range: Touch
\par Target: The character's touched staff
\par Duration: 1 hour/level (D)
\par Saving Throw: None
\par Spell Resistance: No
\par The chara
cter changes a specially prepared quarterstaff into a Huge treantlike creature, about 24 feet tall. When the character concludes the casting of the spell, the character's staff turns into a creature that looks and fights just like a treant. The staff-trea
n
t defends the character and obeys any spoken commands. However, it is not a true treant; it cannot converse with actual treants or control trees. If the staff-treant is reduced to 0 hit points or less, it crumbles to powder and the staff is destroyed. Oth
erwise, the staff can be used as the focus for another casting of the spell. The staff-treant is always at full strength when created, despite any wounds it may have suffered the last time it appeared.
\par Focus: The quarterstaff, which must be specially prepared. Preparing the staff takes 28 days. The character cannot adventure or engage in other strenuous activity during the preparation period.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \i\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Chaos Hammer
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Evocation [Chaotic]
\par Level: Chaos 4
\par Components: V, S
\par Casting Time: 1 action
\par Range: Medium (100 ft. + 10 ft./level)
\par Area: 20-ft.-radius burst
\par Duration: Instantaneous
\par Saving Throw: Will half (see text)
\par Spell Resistance: Yes
\par Only lawful and neutral (not chaotic) creatures are harmed by the spell.
\par The spell deals 1d8 points of damage per two caster levels (maxim
um 5d8) to lawful creatures and staggers them for 1d6 rounds. A staggered character can take only partial actions. A successful Will save reduces the damage by half and negates the stagger effect.
\par The spell deals only half damage against creatures who are neither lawful nor chaotic, and they are not staggered. They can reduce the damage by half again with a successful Will save.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \i\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Charm Monster
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Enchantment (Charm) [Mind-Affecting]
\par Level: Brd 3, Sor/Wiz 4
\par Components: V, S
\par Casting Time: 1 action
\par Range: Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par Target: One living creature
\par Duration: 1 day/level
\par Saving Throw: Will negates
\par Spell Resistance: Yes
\par This charm makes a creature regard the character as a trusted friend and ally. If the creature is currently being threatened or attacked by the character or the character's allies, however, he receives a +5 bonus on his saving throw.
\par The spell does not ena
ble the character to control the charmed creature as if the creature were an automaton, but the subject perceives the character's words and actions in the most favorable way. The character can try to give the subject orders, but the character must win an 
opposed Charisma check to convince the subject to do anything he or she wouldn\rquote 
t ordinarily do. (Retries not allowed.) A charmed creature never obeys suicidal or obviously harmful orders. Any act by the character or the character's apparent allies that thre
atens the charmed creature breaks the spell. Note also that the character must speak the creature\rquote s language to communicate the character's commands, or else be good at pantomiming.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \i\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Charm Person
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Enchantment (Charm) [Mind-Affecting]
\par Level: Brd 1, Sor/Wiz 1
\par Components: V, S
\par Casting Time: 1 action
\par Range: Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par Target: One person
\par Duration: 1 hour/level
\par Saving Throw: Will negates
\par Spell Resistance: Yes
\par This charm makes a humanoid of Medium-size or smaller regard the character as a trust
ed friend and ally. If the creature is currently being threatened or attacked by the character or the character's allies, however, he receives a +5 bonus on his saving throw.
\par The spell does not enable the character to control the charmed person as if the p
erson were an automaton, but the subject perceives the character's words and actions in the most favorable way. The character can try to give the subject orders, but the character must win an opposed Charisma check to convince the subject to do anything h
e or she wouldn\rquote 
t ordinarily do. (Retries not allowed.) A charmed person never obeys suicidal or obviously harmful orders. Any act by the character or the character's apparent allies that threatens the charmed person breaks the spell. Note also that the cha
racter must speak the person\rquote s language to communicate the character's commands, or else be good at pantomiming.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \i\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Charm Person or Animal
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Enchantment (Charm) [Mind-Affecting]
\par Level: Drd 2
\par Target: One person or animal
\par As charm person, except that it can also affect an animal.
\par This charm makes a humanoid or animal of Medium-size or smaller regard the character as a trusted friend and ally. If the creature is currently being threatened or attacked by the character or the character's allies, however, he receives
 a +5 bonus on his saving throw.
\par The spell does not enable the character to control the charmed person as if the person were an automaton, but the subject perceives the character's words and actions in the most favorable way. The character can try to give 
the subject orders, but the character must win an opposed Charisma check to convince the subject to do anything he or she wouldn\rquote 
t ordinarily do. (Retries not allowed.) A charmed creature never obeys suicidal or obviously harmful orders. Any act by the cha
racter or the character's apparent allies that threatens the charmed creature breaks the spell. Note also that the character must speak the creature\rquote s language to communicate the character's commands, or else be good at pantomiming.
\par 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \i\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Chill Metal
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Transmutation [Cold]
\par Level: Drd 2
\par Components: V, S, DF
\par Casting Time: 1 action
\par Range: Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par Target: Metal equipment of one creature/two levels, no two of which can be more than 30 ft. apart; or 25 lb. of metal/level, none of which can be more than 30 ft. away from any of the rest
\par Duration: 7 rounds
\par Saving Throw: Will negates (object)
\par Spell Resistance: Yes (object)
\par Unattended, nonmagical metal gets no saving throw. Enchanted metal is allowed a saving throw against the spell. An item in a creature\rquote s possession uses the creature\rquote s saving throw (unless its own is higher).
\par A creature takes cold damage if its equipment is chilled. It takes full damage if its armor is affected or if it\rquote 
s holding, touching, wearing, or carrying metal weighing one-fifth of its weight. The creature takes minimum damage (1 point or 2 points; see the table) if it\rquote s not wearing metal armor and the metal that it\rquote 
s carrying weighs less than one-fifth of its weight.
\par On the first round of the spell, the metal becomes chilly and uncomfortable to touch but deals no damage (this is also the effect on the last round of the spell\rquote s durat
ion). During the second (and also the next-to-last) round, icy coldness causes pain and damage. In the third, fourth, and fifth rounds, the metal is freezing cold, causing more damage, as shown below:
\par Round \tab Temperature Damage
\par ----- \tab ----------- ------
\par 1 \tab Cold None
\par 2 \tab Icy 1d4 points
\par 3\endash 5 \tab Freezing 2d4 points
\par 6 \tab Icy 1d4 points
\par 7 \tab Cold None
\par Any heat intense enough to damage the creature negates cold damage from the spell (and vice versa) on a point-for-point basis. Underwater, chill metal deals no damage, but ice immediately forms around the affected metal, making it more buoyant.
\par Chill metal counters and dispels heat metal.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \i\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Chill Touch
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Necromancy
\par Level: Sor/Wiz 1
\par Components: V, S
\par Casting Time: 1 action
\par Range: Touch
\par Targets: Creature or creatures touched (up to one/level)
\par Duration: Instantaneous
\par Saving Throw: Fortitude partial
\par Spell Resistance: Yes
\par A touch from the character's hand disrupts the life force of living creatures. Each touch channels negative energy that deals 1d6 points
 of damage and possibly also 1 point of temporary Strength damage. (A successful Fortitude saving throw negates the Strength damage.) The character can use this melee touch attack up to one time per level.
\par Undead touched by the character suffer no damage or Strength loss, but they must make successful Will saving throws or flee as if panicked for 1d4 rounds +1 round per caster level.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \i\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Circle of Death
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Necromancy [Death]
\par Level: Sor/Wiz 6
\par Components: V, S, M
\par Casting Time: 1 action
