\par Saving Throw: None
\par Spell Resistance: Yes
\par This spell creates a Large magic hand. This floating, disembodied hand moves and attacks as directed by the character. (The character directs it as a free action.) The floating hand can move up to 60 feet and can attack in the sam
e round.  Since the hand is directed by the character, its ability to notice or attack invisible or concealed creatures is no better than the character's.  The hand attacks once per round, and its attack bonus equals the character's level + the character'
s
 Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma modifier (for a wizard, cleric, or sorcerer, respectively), +11 for the hand's Strength score (33), -1 for being Large. The hand's damage is 1d8+12, and any creature struck must make a Fortitude save (against this spell'
